## 3. Testing Strategy Overview

### 3.1 Test Pyramid

```
        [End-to-End Tests]        (10-20 scenarios)
       /                        \
      /                          \
     /                            \
    [Integration Tests]           (50-100 tests)
   /                              \
  /                                \
 /                                  \
[Unit Tests]                        (500+ tests)
```

**Unit Tests**: Already exist for plugins and core systems (94% coverage)

**Integration Tests**: New tests for wiring components (this spec)

**End-to-End Tests**: Full system tests with realistic workloads

### 3.2 Test Categories

1. **Smoke Tests**: Basic functionality (5 min)
2. **Functional Tests**: Specific features (30 min)
3. **Performance Tests**: FPS, memory, telemetry overhead (1 hour)
4. **Stress Tests**: High plugin count, extreme parameters (2 hours)
5. **Failure Injection**: Plugin crashes, hardware disconnects (1 hour)
6. **Longevity Tests**: 24-hour continuous run (24 hours)
7. **Agent-Plugin Tests**: Closed-loop communication (1 hour)
8. **Telemetry Validation**: Accuracy and overhead (30 min)
9. **Config/Preset Tests**: Save/load, cloud sync (30 min)
10. **Regression Tests**: Full suite (4 hours)

**Total**: ~36 hours of automated testing

