## 9. Risk Mitigation

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|------------|
| Tests too slow ( >4 hours) | High | Parallelize with pytest-xdist; split into fast/slow suites |
| Flaky tests (non-deterministic) | High | Use fixed seeds; mock time; isolate tests |
| GPU resource contention in CI | Medium | Use GPU quota; run tests sequentially on GPU |
| Long-running tests fail intermittently | Medium | Retry logic; investigate root cause; split into smaller tests |
| Coverage drops | Medium | Enforce minimum coverage; review uncovered code |
| Tests miss real-world bugs | High | Include failure injection; chaos engineering |

